HEADWORD: Homonymously
<hw>Ho*mon"y*mous*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In an
homonymous manner; so as to have the same name or relation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Equivocally; ambiguously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homonymy</ent>⟦br⟧
